      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KISAUNI (1) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close third, 1.5 lengths from the winner PAW PETROV (30.77) at this track. Boasts a strong record from this draw with seven wins and four minor placings from 12 starts. Can go on with it. NOLA KEEPING (4) boasts a consistent overall record including 21 wins from 56 starts, the latest hitting the minor money when third (29.56) over 512m at Mt Gambier. Solid record here at this trip including eight wins. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. WOODSIDE JOHNNY (2) broke from a low draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only a nose (30.68) behind PAW PETROV at this track. Must be included in calculations. TAKE A LITTLE (3) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at her latest outing at this circuit.",
